.START 

Intermark Gaming International Inc. said that Leisure Investments U.S.A. Inc. agreed to sell its majority stake in Intermark to the Camino Trust, an Arizona investor group located in Scottsdale, Ariz. 

Terms of the sale weren't disclosed, but Intermark Gaming said Jacksonville, Fla.-based Leisure Investments had decided to dispose of all its operations outside of the United Kingdom.
Intermark Gaming is a leisure-services concern. 

